The nature of accounting and its types. Legislation. Cash accounting. Bookkeeping of a self-employed person. Accrual basis accounting. Balance sheet. Double-entry accounting and accounts. Accounting of current and fixed assets. Accounting of liabilities and owner equity. Revenues, expenditure, profit, loss. Annual report and annual financial statements. Financial statement analysis. Corporate financial planning. Analysis and management of revenues and expenditure.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide the basic knowledge and terminology of accounting and financial management, and develop analytical abilities and practical problem-solving skills necessary for accounting and financial management.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) knows the basic concepts, methods, legislation and financial reports of accounting and financial management; 2) is able to make basic accounting transactions and financial reports; 3) is able to interpret different financial reports, and associate accounting with other areas of business economy; 4) is able to do financial analysis and make appropriate management decisions; 5) is able to draw up a financial plan and use it as a management instrument; 6) is able to analyse the revenues and expenditure of a company, and make appropriate management decisions.
